                <note rend="inline" type="source">File. No. 812.00/4884.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Nogales</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas, Ariz.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-12T18:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rebels appeared about 3 miles east of Aguaprieta, coming toward Aguaprieta. In
                    view thereof the commanding officer of the United States troops stationed in
                    Douglas stated verbally and personally to the commanding officer of the Federal
                    troops in Aguaprieta that he must prevent bullets fired by the troops under his
                    command from passing into the territory of the United States, and has sent a
                    writen message to the same effect by a civilian courier to the commanding
                    officer of the threatening revolutionary forces.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dye.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
